|GKB-- Scry ------------------------------------------------------|000

A druid may use the Tekali current to create a scrying pool --
a tiny, short-lived pool of water which can be
used to magically locate others.  This is not
foolproof -- even a druid who has both mastered
this invocation and is very wise may be detected by
a perceptive target, and the effort involved in
scrying is not trivial.  Yet it is still considered
a useful talent by those who practice it. Scrying
only works if both you and the object of your
attention are outside, on solid ground, and in
natural settings.

|CKBCommand:      |000 scry <target>
|CKBBase Cost:    |000 20 Tekali nwyfre
|CKBBase Recovery:|000 slow
|CKBBase Effect:  |000 locate
|CKBBase Duration:|000 instant
|CKBGuild Level:  |000 5
